abstract_ssm: This collection consists of the research notes, manuscripts, typescripts, photostats, photographs, lectures, correspondence, and graphic materials of art historian William Sawitzky (1879-1947). Most of the material dates from l930-1947, and documents Sawitzky's extensive research on early American art and artists, including Ralph Earl, Matthew Pratt, and Gilbert Stuart. Later material is the work of his wife, Susan Clay Sawitzky (1897-1981).
